If the top file cannot load and the resulting top env contains only an empty list of items there is no proper warning of such. We need an error if top.sls does not get loaded at all, the best way to check that is if the resulting top env has no items at all.
see the stack overflow http://stackoverflow.com/questions/22368674/no-top-file-or-external-nodes-data-matches-found-with-salt
